Two commuter trains collided in a tragic accident near Los Angeles, resulting in ten deaths and over 100 injuries.
The collision occurred after a suicidal man left his car on the tracks, causing one train to derail and crash into another.
Rescuers worked tirelessly to free passengers trapped in the wreckage, while the city declared a tactical alert to aid in the rescue efforts.
The man responsible, Juan Manuel Alvarez, faced charges of multiple counts of murder.
The incident left the community in shock and mourning, prompting calls for increased safety measures on commuter rail lines.
